radiographic_examinations.findings: Imaged lung bases are clear; liver, spleen, gallbladder, adrenal glands, and pancreas appear grossly normal; kidneys appear unremarkable; abdominal aorta is normal in course and caliber; no lymphadenopathy, free air or free fluid is seen; stomach and duodenum appear normal; loops of small and large bowel demonstrate no signs of ileus or obstruction; the appendix is fluid filled and dilated to 10mm with a hyperdense focus within the proximal appendiceal lumen likely an appendicolith; cecal diverticulum without evidence of cecal diverticulitis; scattered diverticulosis in the distal colon without diverticulitis; uterus and adnexae unremarkable; bladder is empty; no worrisome lytic or blastic osseous lesion seen.
